    "aaw_home_z07_fit": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"aaw-home-shell\">\n  <section class=\"aaw-home-section aaw-home-fit-section\" aria-labelledby=\"aaw-home-fit-title\">\n    <div class=\"aaw-home-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"aaw-home-section-head\">\n        <div>\n          <p class=\"aaw-home-kicker\">FitMorph</p>\n          <h2 id=\"aaw-home-fit-title\">Change the fit. Keep the sound.</h2>\n        </div>\n        <p>The acoustic core stays put. The outer shell comes off. Try a different size, pass them to a bandmate, refit them a year from now - the tuning you bought is the tuning you keep.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"aaw-home-proof-grid\">\n        <figure class=\"aaw-home-proof-image\">\n          <img src=\"{{ 'z07-fitmorph-interchangeable-fit-options-tool.jpg' | asset_img_url: '900x' }}\" alt=\"Z07 FitMorph holders, screws, and acoustic core laid out\" width=\"1856\" height=\"2304\" loading=\"lazy\">\n          <figcaption><b>One core. Interchangeable shells.</b><span>The driver assembly is permanent. Everything around it is not.</span></figcaption>\n        </figure>\n        <div class=\"aaw-home-proof-list\">\n          <article><span>01</span><h3>A seal you can rebuild</h3><p>When the fit goes off - new ear tips, a different commute, two years of wear - swap the shell instead of the monitor.</p></article>\n          <article><span>02</span><h3>No tube between driver and ear</h3><p>Z07's hybrid core fires directly into the canal. No sound bores. No dampening filters in the path. Less compression, more of what the driver does.</p></article>\n          <article><span>03</span><h3>The 2-pin socket lives in the shell</h3><p>Replace a damaged socket without sending the monitor in for service. Cable swaps too - same 0.78mm 2-pin standard the industry uses.</p></article>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
