    "aaw_home_brand_trust": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"aaw-home-shell\">\n  <section class=\"aaw-home-brand-band\">\n    <div class=\"aaw-home-wrap aaw-home-philosophy-wrap\">\n      <p class=\"aaw-home-kicker\">About</p>\n      <blockquote class=\"aaw-home-philosophy\">\n        Listening is where the work starts, and where it returns. It is how a shell becomes comfortable, how a crossover finds its voice, how a stage monitor earns trust, and how a personal IEM becomes the one a listener reaches for without thinking.\n      </blockquote>\n      <blockquote class=\"aaw-home-founder-quote\"><p>A monitor isn't done when it sounds good on a test bench. It's done when someone wears it for four hours on stage and forgets it's there.</p><cite>Kevin Wang, founder</cite></blockquote>\n      <div class=\"aaw-home-founder-bio\" itemscope itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Person\">\n        <p><strong itemprop=\"name\">Kevin Wang</strong> <span itemprop=\"jobTitle\">Founder &amp; Tuning Engineer</span> leads AAW's acoustic design and tuning work in Singapore. Since founding Advanced AcousticWerkes in 2014, his work has focused on custom-fit monitors, universal IEMs, hybrid driver integration, and practical long-term service for musicians, engineers, and audiophiles.</p>\n        <a itemprop=\"sameAs\" href=\"https://sg.linkedin.com/in/kevin-wang-15376265\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Kevin Wang on LinkedIn</a>\n      </div>\n      <p class=\"aaw-home-brand-meta\">AAW &mdash; Singapore, since 2014. <a href=\"/pages/about-us\">The full story &rarr;</a></p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
