        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"aaw-home-shell\">\n  <section class=\"aaw-home-faq-section\" aria-labelledby=\"aaw-home-faq-title\">\n    <div class=\"aaw-home-wrap aaw-home-faq-grid\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"aaw-home-kicker\">FAQ</p>\n        <h2 id=\"aaw-home-faq-title\">Quick answers about AAW.</h2>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"aaw-home-faq-list\">\n        <details open><summary>What does AAW specialize in?</summary><p>Advanced AcousticWerkes specializes in custom and universal in-ear monitors from Singapore. The range covers custom IEMs made from ear impressions, universal-fit monitors such as the Z Series, and long-term support for refits, cables, shells, sockets, and repair work.</p></details>\n        <details><summary>What is the difference between universal and custom IEMs?</summary><p>Universal IEMs use ear tips and can fit many listeners, which makes them easier to demo, share, and travel with. Custom IEMs are made from your ear impressions or approved digital scans, so they seal around your ears only and allow more freedom in shell shape, artwork, and fit tuning.</p></details>\n        <details><summary>Do I need ear impressions for a CIEM?</summary><p>Yes. AAW needs physical impressions from an audiologist or an approved digital ear scan before building a custom in-ear monitor. Accurate impressions are critical because the acoustic seal affects bass, isolation, comfort, and whether the finished monitor can be worn for long sessions.</p></details>\n        <details><summary>Can AAW help with refits or repairs?</summary><p>Yes. The Singapore office handles refit, warranty, repair, cable, socket, and shell service for AAW monitors. If you bought through an authorized dealer, that dealer is often the fastest first stop, but the work is still supported through AAW's service process.</p></details>\n        <details><summary>Where can I audition or order AAW?</summary><p>In Singapore, listeners can start at the AAW office at 76 Playfair Rd, #01-03, or audition through Zeppelin &amp; Co., JABEN, and AV One. Outside Singapore, AAW works with authorized specialist audio dealers; use the store locator or contact sales@acousticwerkes.com for the closest listening point.</p></details>\n        <details><summary>Do you ship internationally?</summary><p>Yes. AAW ships to international customers from Singapore, and available shipping options are shown at checkout based on your country and address. Delivery time depends on whether the monitor is ready-to-ship, made to order, or custom-built from impressions. Import duties, VAT, brokerage fees, and local taxes are set by your destination country and are normally paid by the buyer on arrival. If your country is not available at checkout, contact sales@acousticwerkes.com before ordering.</p></details>\n        <details><summary>Where are AAW monitors manufactured?</summary><p>AAW monitors are designed and tuned from Singapore. Production is handled through AAW's wholly owned lab in Shenzhen, with Singapore-led acoustic reference work, measurement, service, and customer support.</p></details>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>",
